{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn99061530/00332892605/1958011001/0977.xml":{"full_text":"FRIDAY, JANUARY 10, 1958\nCLASSIFIED\nADVERTISING.\nADVERTISING IN THESE COLUMNS COSTS THREE CENTS PER\nWORD, FIRST INSERTION; ALL INSERTIONS AFTER FIRST. TWO\nCENTS PER WORD. MINIMUM CHARGE IS 50 CENTS. IF YOU\nWANT TO BUY, RENT, SELL, SWAP, GET A JOB. HIRE HELP.\nAND SOMETHING LOST. THE CLASSIFIEDS OFFER AN EFFEC\nTIVE AND ECONOMICAL MEDIUM.\nVANN OIL HEATERS with cir\nculating fans for sale. Two\nmodels, $139.00 and $95.00. Cahoon\nand Swindell, Swan Quarter.\nH-12-5-Btc\nHOME IMPROVEMENTS\u2014Roof\ning, siding, garages built, rooms\nadded, baths installed complete,\nbrick and cement work, painting\nor anything else you want to im\nprove your home. Pay nothing\ndown, 36 months to pay. See\nCharles Haskett or phone 5704\nElisabeth City. T-8-9-tfc\nGO2 fire extinguishers, S2O each\nor two for $35. USCG approved.\nG. G. Bonner, General Supply Co.,\nManteo. Tel. 4-W. T-11-8-tfc\nVISIT OUR NURSERY for a va\nriety of flowering plants; shrubs\nand trees for landscaping. Roanoke\nIsland Gardens, cor. Mother Vine\nyard Road and Highway 64, Man\ntea, N. C. Phone 210-J.\nT-10-18-tfc\nOFFICE SUPPLIES. Loose leaf\nledgers, ledger sheets, columnar\nsheets, columnar pads; 200-page\nand 300-page single entry ledgers;\nday books, counter books, type\nwriter ribbon, typewriter erasers,\ntypewriter cleaner, and many oth\ner items needed for daily use in\nyour office. TIMES PRINTING\nCO., Manteo, N. C. Phone 44.\nVisit ANDERSON\u2019S SUPER\nMARKET-BEACH STORE at\ntwo mile post. Vacation headquar\nters. Open year \u2019round. Write\nBILL ANDERSON\u2019S RENTAL\nAGENCY, KITTY HAWK, reser\nvations, oceanfront housekeeping\ncottages. T-4-8-tfc\nTHE OLD SEA CAPTAIN AND\nDRUMMER Book sl, postpaid.\nGet this racy book of dialogue\nfrom Cape Hatteras and the N. C.\nCoastland. Send it to your friends,\n6 copies $5 postpaid. Times Print\ning Co., Inc., Manteo, N. C.\nFor your insurance needs see\nW. R. PEARCE, Manteo, N. C.\nAll kinds of insurance\nOUR SUBSCRIPTION PRICE is\n$3 per year, but for two silver\ndollars, minted prior to the year\n1880, we will give you a year\u2019s\nsubscription to this newspaper.\nMail dollars direct. This offer\ncloses January 31.\n\u25a0V 1 \"r A-\nAZALEAS, CAMELLIAS, SA\nSANQUAS and many other\nbroad leaf evergreens. Container\ngrown plants start at SI.OO each.\n\u201cWe grow the plants we sell.\u2019\u2019\nNance Nursery, four miles east of\nWashington on Pactolus Highway.\nH-l-9-Ste\nINDEPENDENT insurance agen\ncies can and will \u201cserve you\nfirst\u201d Contact us for yours now.\nHugh Fortescue, Washington.\nTPH-8-29-tfc\nARTIFICIAL BREEDING of your\ncows to purebred, proven stocks\nis both profitable and economical.\nThis service available to family\ncow owners, beef producers, dairy\nherds. All dairy and beef breeds\navailable. Call H. E. Clayton, Bel\nhaven WH 3-3206. P-10-4-tfc\nFOR AUTO LIABILITY and fire\ninsurance on Hatteras Island,\nSee Ivey Batten, Hatteras.\nT-l-11-tfc\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY.\nHaving this day duly qualified\nas Administratrix of the estate of\nAngenora P. Berry, deceased, of\nManteo, Dare County, North Car\nolina, I. hereby give notice to all\npersons indebted to her estate to\ncase forward and make immediate\nsettlement; and those holding\nclaims against the said estate will\npresent them for payment within\nTWELVE MONTHS from the date\nof this notice or it will be pleaded\nin bar of their recovery.\nThis 20th day of November,\n1967.\nMRS. GUSSIE E. COLLINS,\nAdmx.\nManteo, North Carolina.\nT-11-29-6tc\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nThe undersigned, having quali\nfied as Administrator with the\nwill annexed of the estate of Julian\nB. Toler, Deceased, late of Dare\nCounty. North Carolina, this is to\nnotify all persons having claims\nagainst said estate to present\nthem to the undersigned in Kitty\nHawk, North Carolina, on or be\nfore the 3rd day of January, 1959,\nor this notice will be pleaded in\nbar of their recovery. All persons\nindebted to said estate will please\nmake immediate payment to the\nundersigned. _\nThis the 30th day of December,\n1957\nPENNEL A. TILLETT,\nAdministrator,\nWith Will Annexed.\nKitty Hawk. N. C.\nT-l-3-6tc\nRUBBER STAMPS made to order.\nStamp pads, daters, inks, etc.\nTimes Printing Co., Inc., Manteo,\nN. C.\nFOR RENT: Two-bedroom house\nin Belhaven; available January\nIst Apply 409 East Pungo Street,\nor phone WHitehall 3-3206.\nP-12-19-tfc\nLEDGERS, Office books, loose\nsheets; typewriter erasers, rib\nbons,- cleaner, Times Office, Man\nteo.\nHELP WANTED.\u2014WANTED AT\nONCE, Rawleigh Dealer in Hyde\nand Tyrrell Counties. Write Raw\nleigh\u2019s, Dept NCA-480-R, Rich\nmond, Va. H-l-2-stp\nMAN OR WOMAN\u2014Established\nWatkins Route available no\nexperience necessary in this area.\nWrite P. O. Box 5071, Department\nS-3, Richmond, Va. P-l-9-4tp\nNOTICE OF THE\nDISSOLUTION OF\nDARE CONCRETE COMPANY.\nINCORPORATED\nTO ALL TO WHOM THESE\nPRESENTS MAY COME\nGREETING:\nTAKE NOTICE, That pursuant\nto the provisions of Section 55-117\nof the General Statutes of North\nCarolina, duly executed Articles of\nDissolution by the unanimous writ\nten consent of all the shareholders\nof DARE CONCRETE COMPANY,\nINCORPORATED, a corporation of\nthe State of North Carolina, whose\nprincipal office is in the Town of\nKill Devil Hills in the County of\nDare, State of North Carolina,\n(Martin Kellogg, Jr., being the\nAgent therein, and in charge there\nof. upon whom process may be\nserved) has been filed in the Of\nfice of the Secretary of State, of\nthe State of North Carolina, on the\n13th day of December, 1957, pur\nsuant, and in compliance with,\nChapter 55 of the General Statutes\nof North Carolina entitled \"Busi\nness Corporation Act\u201d.\nAll creditoi-s of the corporation\nare further notified to file with\nthe corporation statements of all\naccounts and liabilities due them\nby it, pursuant to the provisions of\nGS. 55-119.\nIN TESTIMONY WHEREOF,\nthe DARE CONCRETE COM\nPANY, INCORPORATED, has\ncaused this notice to be executed\nin its name and behalf by its\nPrseident and attested by its Sec\nretary this the 19 day of Dec, 1957.\nDARE CONCRETE COMPANY,\nINCORPORATED\nBy J. P. Sadler, President\nATTEST:\nBachman Doar, Secretary\n-12-27-4tc\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nHaving this day duly qualified\nas Executor of the estate of Anna\nE. Midgett, Deceased, of Waves,\nDare County, North Carolina, I\nhereby give notice to all persons\nindebted to her estate to come for\nward and make immediate settle\nment; and those holding claims\nagainst the said estate will present\nthem for payment within TWELVE\nMONTHS from the date of this\nnotice or it will be pleaded in bar\nof their recovery.\nThis 23rd dav of October, 1957.\nLELAND R. MIDGETT, Executor\nWaves, North Carolina\nT-12-20-6tc\nBEFORE THE\nBOARD OF COMMISSIONERS\nDARE COUNTY\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nRoanoke Sound Shores, Inc.\nPetitioner to\nDare County\nNOTICE OF HEARING\nON A PETITION\nFOR ABANDONMENT\nOF STREET OR WAY\nAll persons having or claiming\nto have any right, title or interest\nin or to lands located in Nags Head\nTownship, Dare County, North\nCarolina, formerly known as Nags\nHead Beach property of Nags Head\nDevelopment Corporation, as shown\non Map or Plat, recorded in Map\nBook 1. pages 192-184, Office of\nthe Register of Deeds, Dare Coun\nty. North Carolina, and the Roa\nnoke Sound Shores Inc. property\nshown on map or plat thereof, re\ncorded in Map Book 2, Page 90,\nPublic Registry of Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, and the public will\ntake notice that a petition has been\nfiled with this Board, the purpose\nof which is to abandon a certain\nstreet, way or right of way dedi\ncated to the public by plat, but\nunopened, unpaved and unused,\nwhich said area is situated to the\nWestward of U. S. Highway No.\n158. commonly known as Virginia\nDare Trail, and running in a\nNorth-South direction, and desig\nnated on the plat of Petitioner\u2019s\nproperty as Monitor Street, a copy\nof said petition is on file with the\nClerk to the Board of Commis\nsioners.\nAnd all such persons will take\nnotice that a hearing upon the Pe\ntition will be had at the February\nmeeting of the Board of Commis\nsioners. in the Court House in\nManteo. N. C. at 10:00 A.M. on\nTuesday. February 4, 1958.\nAnd all interested parties win\nfurther take notice that the Board\nSurvival Is Not Enough\nH\nI*\n\u2022pKS 1 I\nAfter week* in an iron lung, Mr*. Jane Atwood, Ann Arbor, Mich.,\nhousewife, made a dramatic recovery from polio. Her arm* and shoul\nders ar* still paralyzed. But with March of Dime* assistance she got\n17 month* of training at the Ann Arbor Rehabilitation Center, wa\u00bb\nfitted with a modern brace, doe* housework, cares for her two children.\nKITTY HAWK, COLINGTON\nHOME CLUBS TO COMBINE\nThe January meeting of the\nKitty Hawk Home Club was held\nJan. 3rd, at the home of Mrs. Mary\nPerry, with five present.\nMrs. Ida Beasley, Mrs. Horace\nDough. Mrs. Mincie Partridge and\nMrs. Collie Williams of the Coling\nton Club also attended. Mrs. Dough\nsuggested that the two clubs be\nf\nROANOKE ISLAND CLUB\nAND LODGE MEETINGS\nMASONS: Manteo Lodge, Sec\nond and Fourth Monday Evenings,\nin Manteo Town Hall. Wanchese\nLodge, First and Third Thursdays,\nWanchese Lodge Hall.\nEASTERN STAR, Second and\nFourth Thursday evenings in Wan\nchese Lodge Hall.\nODDFELLOWS, Each Tuesday\nevening in Manteo Town Hall.\nREBEKAHS, First and Third\nMonday evenings, Manteo Town\nHall.\nMANTEO ROTARY, each Mon\nday evening, and MANTEO\nLIONS, First and Third Tuesdays\nin Community Building.\nWANCHESE RURJTAN, third\nFridays, Wanchese' schoolhouse.\nDEGREE OF POCAHONTAS;\nSecond and Fourth Fridays. 7:30\np.m., Wanchese Masonic Hall.\nAMERICAN LEGION, Ft Ra\nleigh Post No. 26, 2nd Thursday,\n7:30 p.m., Community Bldg., Man\nteo.\nROANOKE ISLAND GARDEN\nCLUB meets at 2:30 in the after\nnoon, first Thursday of each\nmonth, in the homes of members.\nMANTEO WOMAN\u2019S CLUB,\nsecond Tuesday each month.\nHomes of members, 8 p.m.\nWINTER FERRY SCHEDULES\nEffective Oct. I. 1957. through May 31. 1938\nALLIGATOR RIVER FERRY\nI\u201d. East Lake lv. Tyrrell County\n5:00 A.M. 4:40 A.M.\n7:20 A.M. 8:00 A.M.\n8 40 A.M. 9:20 A.M.\n10:00 10:40 A.M.\n11:20 A.M. 12:00 Noon\n12:40 P.M. 1:20 P.M.\n2:00 P.M. 2:40 P.M.\n3:20 P.M. 4:00 P.M.\n4:40 P.M. 5:20 P.M.\n6:00 P.M. 6:40 P.M.\n7:20 P.M. 8:00 P.M.\nOREGON INLET FERRY\nLv. North Shore tv. South Shore\n(Delete\n6:00 A.M. Dec. 1-Feb. 15) 6:30 A.M.\n6:30 A.M. 7:00 A.M.\n7:00 A.M. 7:30 A.M.\n7:30 A.M. 8:00 A.M.\n8:00 A.M. 8:30 A.M.\n8 30 A.M. 9:00 A.M.\n9:00 A.M. \u00bb:30 A.M.\n9:30 A.M. 10:00 A.M.\n10:00 A.M. 10:30 A.M.\n10:30 A.M. 11:00 A.M.\n11:00 A.M. 11:30 A.M.\n11:30 A.M. 12:00 Noon\n12:00 Noon 12:30 P.M.\n12:30 P.M. 1:00 P.M.\n1:00 P.m. 1:30 P.M.\n1:30 P.M. 2 00 P.M.\n2:00 P.M. 2:30 P M\n2:30 P.M. 3:00 P.M.\n3:00 P.M. 3:30 P.M.\n3:30 P.M. 4:00 P.M.\n4:00 P.M. 4:30 P.M.\n4:30 P.M. 5:00 P.M.\n(Delete\n5:00 P.M. Nov. 1-Jan. 311 5:30 P.M.\n5:30 P.M. (Add March 1) 6:00 P.M.\nHATTERAS INLET FERRY\nlv. Hatteras lv. Ocracoke\n74)0 A.M. p-nn A.M.\n10:00 A.M. 11:00 A.M.\n12:30 P.M. 1:30 P.M.\n3:00 P.M.4:00 P.M.\nwill act on said Petition at its\nFebruary meeting; and that all\ninterested parties shall attend and\nmake protest, if any they have to\nsaid petition, or they will be bound\nby the action of the Board, as by\nlaw provided, unless appeal is duly\nfiled before the said Board.\nNotice is hereby issued by au\nthority and at the direction of the\nBoard at its January meeting\nThis 7th day of January, 1957.\nDARE COUNTY\nBOARD OF COMMISSIONERS\nBy Melvin R. Daniels\nClerk to the Board\nT-l-10-4tc\nTHE COASTLAND TIMES, MANTEO, N. C.\ncombined, feeling that a large club\ncan accomplish much more. Hence\nforth the club will be known as\nthe Kitty Hawk-Colington Club.\nMiss Fran Alexander, Home\nAgent, introduced J. L. Rea, for\nmerly of Lumberton, who is the\nnew Farm Agent for Dare Coun\nty. He gave a talk on \u201cOutlook for\n1958\u201d explaining how, although\nthere are fewer people living on\nfarms, that the size of farms have\nincreased as well as the output\nfrom these farms.\nMiss Alexander explained the\nclub year books and club project\nleaders were elected.\nMiss Alexander gave a demon\nstration on \u201cSelection and Con\nstruction of Window Curtains.\u201d\nThe hostess served apple sauce,\ncake, nuts and coffee.\nThe meeting adjourned to meet\nwith Mrs. Louise Gilley at Avalon\nBeach on Feb. 7th at 11:30 a.m.\nMANNS HARBOR PERSONALS\nDr. and Mrs. John Wright have\nreturned to Chapel Hill after\nspending the New Year\u2019s holidays\nhere.\nMrs. Alice Combs, who resides\nat Winfall, visited friends here\nduring the holidays.\nMr. and Mrs. Herbert Gard,\nClyde Edward and Sherman Lee\nGard of Norfolk were the holiday\nguests of Mrs. Gard\u2019s parents, Mr.\nand Mrs. Sherman Twiford.\nMr. and Mrs. LaSalla Johnson\nof Norfolk spent the week end\nwith Mr. and Mrs. T. H. Midgett.\nMr. and Mrs. Henry Armstrong,\nTommy, Lynn, and Lois Armstrong\nspent the week end in Norfolk,\nwhere they visited Mr. and Mrs.\nJohn Dunbar and and Mr. and Mrs.\nE. L. Armstrong.\nMr. and Mrs. Stanford White\nvisited in Norfolk and Virginia\nBeach during the holidays.\nMr. and Mrs. Charlie Midgett\nhave been in Norfolk, where Mr.\nMidgett has received medical at\ntention.\nMr. and Mrs. Clyde Twiford, Jr.,\nDonna, Debora and Barry Twiford,\nhave returned to their home in\nNorfolk after spending several\ndays with Mrs. Twiford\u2019s parents,\nMr. and Mrs. Preston Twiford, and\nalso visiting Mr. and Mrs. Clyde\nTwiford of Mashoes.\nEdward White of Norfolk visited\nhis mother, Mrs. Wm. White, and\nother relatives here Monday.\nMr. and Mrs. Marvin Beasley\nare returning home this week after\nspending the holidays in Pelzer, S.\nC., where they have been visiting\nMrs. Beasley\u2019s mother, Mrs. Laura\nTessnear.\nMrs. Maybell Mann has been a\npatient in the Columbia Hospital\nfor several days.\nMrs. Iria Ralph returned home\nSunday, after being a patient in\nNorfolk General Hospital.\nMr. and Mrs. Donald Green of\nElizabeth City, were here for the\nweek end. Their daughter, Carol\nAnn, accompanied them home after\nspending last week with her grand\nparents. Mr. and Mrs. Calvin\nBeasley.\nHorace Mann of Portsmouth,\nVa., Allen Mann of Manteo spent\nSunday with Mr. and Mrs. J. F.\nBurrus.\nPvt. Ferrell Gard, USA, who has\nbeen visiting his parents, Mr. and\nMrs. Alton Gard, and grandpar\nents, Mr. and Mrs. H. T. Gibbs,\nleft Sunday for Fort Dix, N. J.\nFrom ther Ferrell will go to Ger\nmany where he will be stationed\nso the next two years.\nRaleigh.\u2014Good news for the\nlady drivers. Os the 1270 drivers\ninvolved in fotal auto wrecks last\nyear only 117 were women, the\nState Department of Motor Ve\nhicles reports.\nSTUMPY POINT PERSONALS\nW.S.C.S. Meets\nMrs. G. M. Kelley was hostess\nto the Woman\u2019s Society of Chris\ntian Service Monday at the Stumpy\nPoint parsonage. Mrs. Ralph\nO\u2019Neal led the worship, her theme,\n\u201cJapan Today\u201d (The March of Mis\nsions in Japan). \u201cDear Lord and\nFather of Mankind\u201d and \u201cWe've a\nStory to Tell to the Nations\u201d were\nsung.\nA challenge \u201cThe I'ried and the\nUntried\u201d was given by leader. Rev.\nG. M. Kelley gave a talk on his\nwork and the Christian growth and\ncivilization of China.\nAfter the business session the\nhostess served sandwiches, dates\nand nuts roll, coffee and cokes to\nthe- 12 present\nM.Y.F.\nThe M.Y.F. is going forward in\nall phases of its program. Officers\nelected in December showing re\nnewed interest and activity. Sev\neral improvements have been made*\nat the recreation center, \u2014well at\ntended and chaperoned by members\nof the church.\nSeveral projects for civic im\nprovement have been discussed,\nalso plans to improve and beautify\nthe church. A cover for the lectern\nhas been ordered. An electric organ\nhas been placed in the church on\ntrial and for observation. The\nyoung people are interested in pur\nchasing an organ for the church\nand are making plans for raising\nthe funds.\nThe community shows pride in\nits young people and will cooperate\nin any way in making a better com\nmunity and better citizens. Much\ncredit for helping promote this\nwork goes to the boys at the Navy\nbarracks.\nMrs. Louise Allen and Mrs. Ma\nbel Payne spent Monday and Tues\nday in Norfolk.\nMr. and Mrs. Hollis Quidley,\nJoan and Darlene of Norfolk visit\ned Mr. and Mrs. Ralph O\u2019Neal and\nAlf Hooper over the week end.\nMr. and Mrs. Dwight Hooper,\nBetty Jo, W. D. Jr. and Davis of\nNorfolk visited Mr. and Mrs. R.\nD. Wise and Alf Hooper Saturday\nand Sunday.\nMrs. U. G. Wise is improving\nfrom a recent illness, but is still\na bed patient. Her many friends\nwish her a speedy recovery.\nArtis Payne of Oceana, Va., vis\nited here Monday and Tuesday.\nMajor Hooper of Baltimore spent\nThursday and Friday with his\nmother, Mrs. Florine Hooper, and\nother relatives.\nLinda Wise visited Sandra Jo\nBell in Norfolk,\nBobby Wise, U.S.C.G., stationed\nin Morehead City and Miss Evelyn\nWilliams of Swan Quarter visited\nhere Sunday with Mr. and Mrs.\nLeland Wise.\nMr. and Mrs. Willie Etheridge\nof Wanchese visited Mr. and Mrs.\nGeo. Payne Sunday.\nMr. and Mrs. Joe Midgett are\nvisiting their daughter, Mrs. Carl\nMason in Norfolk.\nBobby Midgette returned from\nNorfolk Sunday after an tonsillec\ntoihy in Leigh Memorial Hospital.\nEddie Leigh Hooper visited\nI Georgie Wise and Mike Butler in\nNorfolk.\nMrs. Geo. Wise Sr. is visiting\nMrs. Plum Pedrick at Lake Land\ning. Mrs. Pedrick had a stroke re\ncently.\nNOTICE!\nTO DARE COUNTY\nTAXPAYERS\nThe Tax Books for the year 1957 are now in\nmy hands for the collection of taxes. We urge\nyou to pay your taxes now and thus avoid the\npenalty which will begin on February 1.\nA PENALTY OF 1% WILL BE ADDED ON 1957 TAXES\nNOT PAID BEFORE FEBRUARY 2. ANOTHER 1% WILL BE\nADDED MARCH 2 AND AN ADDITIONAL \u00a52 OF 1%\nWILL BE ADDED FOR EACH ADDITIONAL MONTH TAXES\nARE UNPAID.\nF. M. CAHOON\nSHERIFF .and TAX COLLECTOR\nMANTEO, N. C.\nFRISCO PERSONALS\nMr. and Mrs. Jatkie Rollinson\nand daughter visited here recently\nwith Mn and Mrs. Leonard Rollin\nson.\nThe Rev. Ray Sparrow, Red Rol\nlinson, John and Adrian Austin,\nhunted a few days last week in\nHyde County; also visiting Mr.\nSparrow\u2019s parents near Belhaven\nand John and Adrian\u2019s sister, Mrs.\nFerney Rose in New Bern and\nMax Mann in Washington.\nMrs. Betty Conner and daughter\nleft Friday for their home in Wil\nmington. after visiting Mrs. Con-\nNotice of Special Ejection\nAnd New Registration\nin the\nTOWN OF KILL DEVIL HILLS\nUPON THE QUESTION OF THE REPEAL OF THE\nCHARTER OF THE TOWN OF KILL DEVIL HILLS\nA special election will be held on Saturday, March\n15, 1958, between 6:30 o'clock A.M. and 6:30 o'clock\nP.M., Eastern Standard Time, at which there shall be sub\nmitted to the qualified voters of the Town of Kill Devil\nHills, the question of the repeal of the Charter of the\nTown of Kill Devil Hills, and every part and clause thereof\nin its entirety as same is contained in and incorporated by\nChapter 220 of the Session Laws of 1953 General Assem\nbly of North Carolina, entitled \"An Act to Incorporate\nthe Town of Kill Devil Hills in Dare County\".\nA new registration has been ordered and no one will\nbe permitted to vote in said special election unless regis\ntered anew. The books for such new registration will be\nopen between the hours of 9:00 o'clock A.M., and 9:00\no'clock P.M., beginning Saturday, February 15, 1958, and\nbetween the hours of 9:00 o'clock A.M., and 5:00 o'clock\nP. M. on each day thereafter (Sundays exxcepted), and\nclose on Saturday, March I, 1958, at 9:00 o'clock P.M.\nThe said books shall be kept open upon seven (7) days\nbetween the hours of 9:00 o'clock A.M. and 5:00 o'clock\nP.M. (Sundays excepted) preceding the day for closing\nthe registration books on March I, 1958, as aforesaid. On\neach Saturday during such registration period such books\nshall be open at the polling place hereinafter designated\nand shall remain open until 9:00 o'clock P.M.\nSaturday, March I, 1958, is Challenge Day.\nThe polling place and the names of the election\nofficers subject to change as provided by law, are as\nfollows:\nPOLLING PLACE REGISTRAR\nKill Devil Hills Town Hall Mrs. Jean Perry Beacham\nKill Devil Hills, N. C. Kill Devil Hills, N. C.\nJUDGES:\nMrs. Bessie Partridge Mrs. Helen Parker\nKill Devil Hills, N. C. Kill Devil Hills, N. C.\nBy order of the Board of Commissioners for the Town\nof Kill Devil Hills.\nROBERT A. YOUNG\nMayor\nE. V. MELSON\nCommissioner\nR. E. PARKER, JR.\nCommissioner\nR. H. COOK\nCommissioner\nl-10-4tc\nner\u2019s mother, Mrs. C. H. Fulcher.\nMrs. Dennit Ransom left Friday\nto enter the U. S. Public Hospital\nfor treatment.\nDarlene Willis celebrated her\n9th birthday Jan. 4th. Deanna afd\nVerna Gunter, Dianne and Ronnie\nWilliams, Maria Barnett and De\nlores Whedbee spent the afternoon\nwith her playing games and enjoy\ning refreshments of cola\u2019s, cookies,\ncandy and grapes.\nJohn Austin, Mr. and Mrs. R. D.\nBasnett were in Manteo Monday.\nRev. Ray Sparrow and Adrian\nAustin were in Elizabeth City\nTuesday.\nPAGE SEVEN","height":"25676","width":"18391"}}
